INSERT INTO `comments` (`comment_id`, `guide_id`, `name`, `score`, `comment`, `created_at`) VALUES
(4, 10, 'Mary', 4, 'Wow, just finished reading the Lake Bled Travel Guide and I\'m already dreaming of visiting! The guide is packed with useful info and stunning photos. I\'ve never been to Bled, but it\'s definitely on my bucket list now. The walk around the lake sounds amazing, and I can\'t wait to capture those picture-perfect views from the Ojstrica viewpoint. And let\'s not forget about the famous Bled Cream Cake—I\'m already drooling! The guide also mentioned Vintgar Gorge, which looks like a must-visit spot. Overall, the guide was super helpful and has me excited to plan my trip to Lake Bled. Highly recommended!', '2023-06-06 17:27:36'),
(5, 7, 'Sarah', 4, 'Having visited Marrakech myself, I can confidently say that this 3-day itinerary captures the essence of the city perfectly! It covers all the must-visit attractions and the tips on dressing conservatively are helpful, especially for female travelers. I personally loved exploring the vibrant Medina, bargaining in the souks, and enjoying rooftop views while savoring delicious meals. The inclusion of Gueliz as a break from the traditional Medina is a great suggestion. My additional tip for travelers would be to try traditional Moroccan dishes like tagine and couscous for an authentic culinary experience. Enjoy your trip to Marrakech!', '2023-06-06 18:25:10'),
(7, 7, 'Alex', 5, 'Marrakech, here I come! Just got my plane tickets and I´m super stoked about my summer adventure. This post has got me pumped up even more. It covers all the cool stuff to do in Marrakech.\r\n\r\nSo, fellow travelers, any tips on the coolest festivals or events happening in Marrakech during the summer? I want to dive deep into the local culture and have an unforgettable experience. Let me know if you´ve got any suggestions!', '2023-06-06 18:35:06'),
(8, 4, 'Carlos R.', 5, 'Wow, Bogotá looks absolutely amazing! The mix of old and new, the vibrant markets, and the stunning views from Monserrate Mountain have me itching to visit. The energy of La Candelaria is so enticing, and I can´t wait to get lost in its colorful streets. Bogotá, brace yourself, ´cause I´m coming for ya! Thanks for this awesome guide!', '2023-06-06 18:42:09'),
(9, 5, 'John and Anna', 4, 'Hey there!\r\n\r\nJohn and Anna here, and we couldn´t be more thrilled about our upcoming honeymoon in Lisbon! This guide has been a lifesaver in helping us plan our adventure in this beautiful European city. We´ve always wanted to explore Lisbon together, and this itinerary seems like the perfect way to make the most of our time.\r\n\r\nQuestion: Is there a particular neighborhood in Lisbon that you would recommend for a romantic evening stroll?\r\n\r\nIf you have any additional recommendations or tips for our honeymoon, we´d love to hear them. We´re open to any suggestions to make our trip even more special. Thank you!', '2023-06-08 16:11:53'),
(14, 17, 'Hagrid', 5, 'Blimey, would ya look at all this fancy technology! It\'s like pure magic, it is! I\'ve seen my fair share of strange creatures and powerful spells, but these Muggle gadgets leave me gobsmacked. How do these tiny boxes hold the knowledge of the world? It\'s like havin\' a whole library in the palm o\' your hand! I reckon there\'s a bit o\' enchantment at play here, even if it\'s not the wand-waving kind. Makes me wonder what other magical marvels these Muggles have up their sleeves. Fascinatin\' times we\'re livin\' in, indeed!', '2023-06-09 12:51:50'),
(15, 18, 'Michael McCarthy', 4, 'The Eiffel Tower is definitely the heart and soul of Paris! A quick Paris trip for us started with a hotel near the Eiffel Tower, we discovered that everything starts at the tower. Even the Bus from Charles de Gaulle Airport goes to the Eiffel Tower.', '2023-06-10 12:52:08'),
(16, 5, 'Shirley', 5, 'Nice and clear article about Lisbon! I will go to Lisbon at Thursday till Monday. Thanks for this great recommendations! :-)', '2023-06-10 13:44:23'),
(17, 5, 'Adam Hill', 5, 'I’m planning a backpacking trip across Europe for next summer and Lisbon is now totally on the list! Thanks for the help!', '2023-06-10 13:46:50'),
(18, 20, 'Nicole', 5, 'Just stopping by to say I absolutely adore your travel guides! On my way to Southeast Asia next week and you’ve provided such great recommendations. Thanks a million!', '2023-06-10 16:19:37'),
(19, 24, 'Katniss Everdeen', 5, 'Hi! Thank you for this itinerary it’s been really helpful for us to plan our trip to Jordan. We’d like to combine an Egypt itinerary with Jordan. Do you have any trips to travel between the two?', '2023-06-16 09:52:02'),
(20, 24, 'Ariahna', 5, 'Hi,<br />\r\nI am interested in doing a Jordan trip sometime in the Spring. Would you be able to recommend a reputable tour company to book with to do a day tour to Petra from Amman? With that being said, are there any hotels in Amman you would recommend that I consider staying at or neighborhoods that are good for tourists to stay in?', '2023-06-16 10:35:07'),
(21, 19, 'Brooke Raboutou', 5, 'What an incredible place to escape to! I loved reading your words and then seeing the pictures to match your descriptions. This looks like a grand adventure!', '2023-06-19 09:40:51'),
(22, 19, 'Kat', 4, 'Really love reading your posts… and this particular post made me fall in love with Sri Lanka all over again. I had been to SL twice but missed out on this epic train journey and the tea plantations. I might go back to SL in 2024', '2023-06-19 09:42:05'),
(23, 19, 'Deborah Patterson', 5, 'Oh, we love a good train journey, and your post has brought a smile to my face as I remember finding the sweet spot of an open doorway on a long, delayed train journey in India.', '2023-06-19 09:43:30'),
(24, 19, 'Paul Horseman', 5, 'You bring journeys to life with your storytelling, but I’m not sure train travel in Sri Lanka is for me. I’d struggle with the lack of comfort, the crowds and the unsureness of knowing what’s going on re tickets and boarding etc…', '2023-06-19 09:44:51'),
(25, 5, 'Hilary', 5, 'We also spent three days in Lisbon, but were pleasantly surprised and wished for more time… I thought I was in shape until my calves told me differently the morning of the second day.', '2023-06-19 18:18:53'),
(26, 18, 'Daniel Dempster-Smith', 5, 'I visited Paris on multiple occasions and it’s one of my favorite capitals in Europe. I have to say, I’m impressed with how much you covered in just three days. I hope you get the chance to visit again and stay a bit longer though. Thank you for this lovely read and keep up the great work', '2023-06-19 18:31:05'),
(27, 18, 'Sinjana Ghosh', 5, 'Paris is amazing! I believe you can see a lot in three days. Their metro line is very handy, and we were able to tour most of these places in couple days. But… there is always more. After you have seen the most famous places, you will discover more and more places in Paris that you would like to see. It is just such an interesting city I think.', '2023-06-19 18:32:10'),
(28, 18, 'Emma', 5, 'You sold it to me within the first few paragraphs! France has never interested me until lately, I’m your typical tourist so for this reason alone I need to go check out pretty much all the above! Have pinned for future reference in case we do decide to book a trip to Paris', '2023-06-19 18:38:20'),
(29, 7, 'Ellie', 5, 'What a detailed and informative post! Marrakech is a fascinating city and it is on my bucket list to visit. I learned a lot. Thank you.', '2023-06-19 18:45:38');

